01/10/2010
TIRANA, Albania -- The ruling Democratic Party (DP) lost a lawmaker on Thursday (September 30th), bringing its number of members in parliament to 67. Lawmaker Paulin Sterkaj abandoned the DP and joined the opposition, citing bad governance, corruption and conflicts of interest in which the government is allegedly involved. Sterkaj represents the region of Shkodra. (Top Channel, Balkan Web, NOA, Shekulli - 30/09/10)
